("SUMO SQUATS", "https://bit.ly/2RQr87u", "Tone your glutes and quads with this easy exercise.", "Toning", "No equipment needed", "Stand with your feet wide, toes pointing out. Bend your knees, lowering your hips deeply, so your thighs are parallel with the floor. Then rise back up, straightening the legs completely and squeezing the glutes at the top of the movement to get the most from the exercise.", "3 reps", "20 sets", "10 minutes", false, false),
("SQUATS", "https://bit.ly/2sp0zIg", "Squats are a great exercise to strengthen and increase flexibility in your knees, calves and glutes.", "Strengthening muscles", "No equipment needed", "Start with your feet hip distance apart, toes pointing forward. Let your body lean slightly forward and engage your abdominals as you bend your knees as though you're sitting down. Hold for about five seconds, and then rise back up to your start position.", "10 reps", "2 sets", "20 minutues", true, false),
("BRIDGE", "https://bit.ly/2FqwGjd", "This exercise strengthens several muscles groups at once.", "Strengthening muscles", "No equipment needed", "Start by lying on your back, arms by your sides, palms facing down. Your knees are bent with feet flat on the floor, hip distance apart. Inhale, press your feet into the floor and lift your glutes straight up off the floor as high as you can without arching your back. Hold for about five seconds, and then lower back down to the floor.", "10 reps", "3 sets", "10 minutues", true, false),
("LUNGES", "https://bit.ly/2VS7x60", "Think of lunges as an exaggerated walk.", "Strengthening muscles", "No equipment needed", "Standing tall with your feet hip distance apart and toes pointing forward, take a big step forward while letting your back knee bend toward the floor without touching it. Use your front leg to push yourself back up to your start position. If you need a little help, simply place one hand on the wall.", "10 reps", "3 sets", "15 minutues", true, false),
("TOE DIPS", "https://bit.ly/2McJcni", "This is a great exercise that will strengthen your deep core muscles, as well as your hip flexors.", "Strengthening muscles", "No equipment needed", "Start by lying on your back with your feet flat on the floor, hip distance apart. Without letting your body shift, engage your abdominals and exhale while bringing your right leg up into a table top position (90 degree angle). Take a breath and bring your left leg up to meet it. Hold for about five seconds, and then slowly place your right leg back down, followed by your left. Repeat, switching up the starting leg each time.", "10 reps", "2 sets", "20 minutues", true, false);





